-- Alstom May Buy Back Converteam From Barclays, LBO France, Challenges Says
-- B y   S t e v e   R h i n d s
-- 2010-10-06T14:00:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/alstom-may-buy-back-converteam-unit-challenges-reports.html
Alstom SA is studying a plan to buy
back Converteam, a former unit sold by the company in 2006,
weekly magazine Challenges reported, without saying where it got
the information.  Converteam, which has annual revenue of 1.15 billion euros,
is currently owned by Barclays Private Equity and LBO France,
Challenges said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Rhinds at 
 srhinds@bloomberg.net  